\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces DGSAR system architecture. Stages~1--3 (top row) handle data ingestion, preprocessing, and decomposition. Stages~4--6 (bottom row) perform model selection, forecasting, and diagnostic validation. Stage~6 implements the diagnostic gate: if Ljung-Box or ACF tests fail, the pipeline loops back to Stage~4 with increased order bounds (dashed red arrow), up to three retries.}}{5}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:architecture}{{1}{5}{DGSAR system architecture. Stages~1--3 (top row) handle data ingestion, preprocessing, and decomposition. Stages~4--6 (bottom row) perform model selection, forecasting, and diagnostic validation. Stage~6 implements the diagnostic gate: if Ljung-Box or ACF tests fail, the pipeline loops back to Stage~4 with increased order bounds (dashed red arrow), up to three retries}{figure.1}{}}
